<TITLE> Poultry show, seminar begin Thursday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 3 (bdnews24.com)  A three-day International Poultry Show and Seminar is beginning Thursday in an effort to fulfil the country's protein demand. President of the World Poultry Science Association (WPSA) Moshiur Rahman told a briefing Tuesday at the National Press Club about 37 articles would be presented at the seminar to be held at Bangladesh-China Friendship Conference Centre. This is the sixth arrangement of the WPSA, he added. Several demands have been raised for the development of the poultry industry. These include the declaration of Poultry Week, providing loan facilities to the poultry farmers facing losses from bide flu, introduction of poultry insurance and making it a habit for children to eat egg at school. They also demanded the launch of a national campaign to sensitise the people about the poultry industry. bd
